data.meta_description: Drew Sidora chats with ET about her sophomore season of 'The Real Housewives of Atlanta,' and the déjà vu moments from season 13 that played out in premiere regarding her marriage with Ralph Pittman. Drew defends Ralph from potential haters and shares an update on where their relationship stands after the drama with his assistant crossing boundaries. The 'Step Up' actress also discusses her bond with the cast, praising Kenya Moore for proving herself to be a friend after being in frenemy territory last year. On the flipside, Drew explains the friction between she and Shereé Whitfield, who Drew claims didn't even give her a chance to win over. Drew also teases her falling out with fast friend Sanya Richards-Ross, who Drew says switched to the 'wrong team' halfway through filming. The star also clarifies her comments about losing 25 lbs. in three weeks and teases what's to come in season 14. 'The Real Housewives of Atlanta' airs Sundays on Bravo.
